--TEST--
Security advisory matching direct dependency preventing a successful update.
--COMPOSER--
{
    "name": "acme/project",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "require": {
        "acme/library": "1.0.0"
    },
    "config": {
        "audit": {
            "block-abandoned": true
        }
    },
    "repositories": [
        {
            "type": "package",
            "package": [
                {
                    "name": "acme/library",
                    "version": "1.0.0",
                    "abandoned": true,
                    "source": { "reference": "some.branch", "type": "git", "url": "" }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
--RUN--
update -v

--EXPECT-EXIT-CODE--
2

--EXPECT-OUTPUT--
Loading composer repositories with package information
Updating dependencies
Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.

  Problem 1
    - Root composer.json requires acme/library 1.0.0 (exact version match: 1.0.0 or 1.0.0.0), found acme/library[1.0.0] but these were not loaded, because they are abandoned.

